grass.n.01.defn: narrow-leaved green herbage: grown as lawns; used as pasture for grazing animals; cut and dried as hay

grass.n.02.defn: German writer of novels and poetry and plays (born 1927)

supergrass.n.01.defn: a police informer who implicates many people

eatage.n.01.defn: bulky food like grass or hay for browsing or grazing horses or cattle

film_editing.n.01.defn: the activity of selecting the scenes to be shown and putting them together to create a film

cutting.n.02.defn: a part (sometimes a root or leaf or bud) removed from a plant to propagate a new plant through rooting or grafting

expl: his cutting of the cake made a terrible mess
cut.n.17.defn: the act of cutting something into parts

cutting.n.04.defn: a piece cut off from the main part of something

expl: he searched through piles of letters and clippings
clipping.n.01.defn: an excerpt cut from a newspaper or magazine

carving.n.02.defn: removing parts from hard material to create a desired pattern or shape

expl: he insisted that we give him the last cut before every deal
the cutting of the cards soon became a ritual
cut.n.15.defn: the division of a deck of cards before dealing

expl: his cut in the lining revealed the hidden jewels
cut.n.16.defn: the act of penetrating or opening open with a sharp edge

expl: the cutting of whiskey with water
the thinning of paint with turpentine
the barber gave him a good cut
cut.n.18.defn: the act of shortening something by chopping off the ends

path.n.03.defn: an established line of travel or access

road.n.01.defn: an open way (generally public) for travel or transportation
